errors.name: InvalidAuthorityAddress
errors.msg: The authority address does not match the provided configuration authority

errors.name: MissingNewAuthority
errors.msg: No new authority provided in remaining accounts

errors.name: SameAuthority
errors.msg: New authority cannot be the same as the current authority

errors.name: MissingNewDeveloper
errors.msg: No new developer provided in remaining accounts

errors.name: SameDeveloper
errors.msg: New developer cannot be the same as the current developer

errors.name: MissingNewToken
errors.msg: No new token account provided in remaining accounts

errors.name: DefaultTokenKey
errors.msg: Token account cannot have the default public key

errors.name: SameToken
errors.msg: New token account cannot be the same as the current token account

errors.name: InvalidTokenProgram
errors.msg: Token account must be owned by the SPL Token or Token-2022 program

errors.name: SameFees
errors.msg: New fee structure cannot be the same as the current fee structure

errors.name: InvalidFeeRecipient
errors.msg: Invalid fee recipient: must be the developer

errors.name: InvalidProtocolToken
errors.msg: Protocol token mint does not match the configured mint

errors.name: FeeRequired
errors.msg: Fee is required but not paid

errors.name: InvalidFeeChoice
errors.msg: Cannot pay a fee that is not configured in the system

errors.name: ZeroAmount
errors.msg: Stream amount must be greater than zero

errors.name: InvalidExtensionValues
errors.msg: New extension values must be greater than existing ones

errors.name: InvalidStreamAuthority
errors.msg: The provided stream authority does not match the expected authority

errors.name: StreamIsImmutable
errors.msg: The stream is immutable and cannot be modified

errors.name: StreamPendingComputation
errors.msg: There is already a pending computation for this stream

as anchor does not support tuples and tuple structs yet.

types.name: MXEAccount
docs: A MPC Execution Environment.

types.name: NodeRef
docs: A reference to a node in the cluster.
The offset is to derive the Node Account.
The current_total_rewards is the total rewards the node has received so far in the current
epoch.

types.name: Output
docs: An output of a computation.
We currently don't support encrypted outputs yet since encrypted values are passed via
data objects.

types.name: Parameter
docs: A parameter of a computation.
We differentiate between plaintext and encrypted parameters and data objects.
Plaintext parameters are directly provided as their value.
Encrypted parameters are provided as an offchain reference to the data.
Data objects are provided as a reference to the data object account.

types.name: WithdrawOutput

as anchor does not support tuples and tuple structs yet.
